<ul>
<li>For those of you missing the Launchpad in macOS 26. Here is a free alternative. <a href="https://www.launchie.app/" target="_blank">Launchie</a>. I use <a href="https://www.alfredapp.com/" target="_blank">Alfred</a> for launching applications, and a whole host of other tasks.</li>
<li>Another person doing a deep dive into Emacs. <a href="https://beardystarstuff.net/posts/2025-08-19.html" target="_blank">Apple to GNULinux Journal - GNU Emacs</a>.</li>
<li>Learn keyboard commands. <a href="https://keybegin.toolooz.com/mac" target="_blank">KeyBegin - Magic Keyboard for Mac (Interactive)</a></li>
<li>Another clipboard manager for the macOS. This is free. <a href="https://www.pastebar.app/" target="_blank">PasteBar - Limitless, Free Clipboard Manager for Mac and Windows. Copy smarter, paste faster.</a></li>
<li>Interesting UI. <a href="https://kando.menu/" target="_blank">Kando - Do things with utmost efficiency!</a></li>
<li>A love letter to BBEdit. <a href="https://thejollyteapot.com/2025/09/05/why-i-love-bbedit/" target="_blank">Why I love BBEdit</a></li>
</ul>
